# 6. バンド、やってみない？

Saki: Is everybody ready?
Saki: Hold on... How do we start?
Shiho: Sigh... Honami, count us in.
Honami: O-Okay. Here it goes... One, two, three, four!
Ichika: (It's the first time we've played together since that time at Saki's house.)
Ichika: (We struggled to keep pace with each other then, but everyone was doing their best, and it was a lot of fun.)
Saki: (I'm loving this! Everyone's parts are coming together in this song! Maybe we could start a band again, and things between us could be the way they used to be...)
Shiho: Stop.
Ichika: What?
Shiho: Ichika, Saki, you're falling behind. Follow Honami's beat.
Ichika: S-Sorry...
Shiho: This is precisely why I didn't want to do this.
Saki: B-But wasn't it sort of good, considering? We actually synched up really well at the start!
Shiho: I'm not interested in playing sort of good. You should know that.
Honami: Sh-Shiho, there's no need to get so worked up about this. Let's try again, from the beginning. Okay?
Miku: Would you mind if I joined you this time?
Ichika: You want to play with us?
Miku: Yes. Do you not want me to?
Ichika: What, no, I didn't mean it like that... It would be amazing, if you're really okay playing with us?
Miku: Watching you play made me want to pick up an instrument too.
Shiho: Sigh... Whatever. Let's just get this over with.
Honami: Okay, I'll start again. One, two, three, four!
Shiho: (!!)
Honami: (Wow... Miku joined in so seamlessly...)
Saki: (And somehow her playing's encouraging everyone!)
Ichika: (She really is something else...)
Miku: Thank you for letting me join in. I could tell that this song means a lot to you.
Shiho: .....
Ichika: (Shiho and Honami both remembered how to play this song.)
Ichika: (Could it be they too hoped that one day, we'd... Maybe that's just wishful thinking.)
Shiho: Okay, are we done? Because I want to go back.
Saki: Wait!
Shiho: What is it now?
Saki: Shiho, Hona, Ichi... Let's get the band back together!
Ichika: !!
Honami: Us, together?
Shiho: Are you joking?
Saki: Oh come ON, we had so much fun just now, right? Wasn't it fun, Shiho?
Shiho: No, it wasn't...
Saki: Even Miku noticed this song has a special place in our hearts. I think that you and Honami actually liked playing it, even though you won't admit it!
Honami: .....
Shiho: I don't want to be in a band with you. Period.
Ichika: Shiho...
Honami: I'm sorry but I don't think I want to do this either.
Saki: Hona... You, too...
Ichika: (I knew it seemed too easy...)
Shiho: I've had enough. Tell me how to get out of here.
Miku: Of course. You did as promised, and I'll keep my word.
Miku: You all played a track just before you appeared here, remember? Called Untitled.
Miku: Untitled is the gateway to this world. Play it to be transported here, stop it to leave.
Ichika: So it was that track...
Shiho: That silent track got us here? Whatever, at least now I can get back out.
Shiho: Bye.
Honami: Then I'll be going too.
Saki: Oh...
Saki: Looks like we're not all friends anymore...
Ichika: .....
Miku: Are you giving up?
Ichika: Huh?
Miku: Are you sure they don't want to be friends?
Saki: You're right. If I give up now, we'll lose any chance we might have at getting back together.
Saki: I don't have a plan or anything, but I'm not giving up, that's for sure!
Miku: That's the way. And if you want to play together again, you can come here anytime.
Ichika: ... Miku, can I ask you something?
Miku: Yes?
Ichika: Why are you here?
Miku: Songs are crystallizations of feelings.
Ichika: Huh? Um, right...
Miku: Just like SEKAI, songs are born from feelings.
Miku: You and your friends need to find out what your true feelings are for them to turn into a song.
Miku: And I'm here to help guide you towards that truth.
Ichika: You're going to help us figure out our feelings...
Miku: I hope you can do it soon. You, and your friends.
